<section class="reviews" id="reviews">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section__title" data-i18n="reviews.title">What people who've already passed are saying</h2>
    <p class="section__subtitle" data-i18n="reviews.subtitle">They started exactly where you are now.</p>
    <div class="reviews__grid">
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card1.text">I failed the test twice — it wasn't the concepts that tripped me up, it was the English wording. Once every question came with a translation right beside it, everything clicked. I passed.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Carmen R.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card1.source">Spanish</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card2.text">I was afraid I'd never keep hundreds of terms in my head. My saved words came back on their own, right as I was starting to forget them — on exam day I remembered all of them.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Dmitry K.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source">Русский</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card3.text">The legal terms in English were a wall for me. With the audio and the translation together, you hear it and understand it right away. The material stopped being intimidating.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Mei L.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card3.source">Chinese</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card4.text">In other apps the explanations were English-only — I understood about half of them. Here the "here's why" goes line by line with a translation: you learn the logic instead of memorizing the right letter.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>João P.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card4.source">Portuguese</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card5.text">Between work and family, there's barely any time to study. I listened to questions on my commute and at the gym, and the study hours just added up on their own. I passed.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Aisha M.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card5.source">Arabic</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card6.text">I had no idea where to start — the sheer volume was scary. The app found my gaps on its own and told me what to study next. I passed on my first try.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Sofia V.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card6.source">Spanish</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
